This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptation of context modeling methods, which is a common topic in the CL community. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as semantic parsing is a task that falls under the umbrella of AI. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper evaluates 13 different context modeling methods, which involves training and testing machine learning models. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as some of the context modeling methods evaluated in the paper involve neural networks. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the challenge of modeling context in semantic parsing, which is a task that is closely related to information retrieval.
